node.text: Travis Barker recently overcame his fear of flying to take his first trip on a plane in 13 years — and it's all thanks to the support of girlfriend Kourtney Kardashian. ❤️ "I said, 'Well, when the day comes you want to fly, I'm telling you I'll do it with you. I would do anything with you. And just give me 24 hours notice.' And that's what she did," the blink-182 drummer said. 🙏 Tap the bio link for more on his romance with the Poosh founder. | 📷: Photopix/GC Images

node.text: Cathey Stoner has more than earned the title of "Best Aunt" after giving birth to her new nephew, John Ryder Sharp. 💕 What had started as a quick joke between twin siblings became reality when Stoner's sister, Sarah Sharp, was diagnosed with choriocarcinoma, a rare and aggressive form of cancer in the uterus, they tell PEOPLE. When Stoner told Sharp that "if you want to grow your family, I would love to do that," Sharp says that it was "the biggest act of love I've ever received — pure, unconditional love." 🙏 Tap the bio link for their incredible story. | 📷: Katelyn Brown

node.text: Jessica Chastain and Oscar Isaac's friendly red carpet appearance at the Venice Film Festival may have taken the Internet by surprise, but the costars have been close friends for decades. ❤️ "Oscar I've known for 20 years. We went to college together," Chastain tells PEOPLE of her Scenes from a Marriage costar. "We have the same process." Tap the bio link for more on their longtime friendship — and why she had to change Isaac's name in her phone during filming. | 📷: Vittorio Zunino Celotto/Getty, Stephane Cardinale - Corbis/Corbis via Getty

node.text: Jennifer Lopez and Ben Affleck have arrived at the Venice Film Festival! ✨ The couple arrived together at the annual event in Italy ahead of Friday's premiere for Ridley Scott's The Last Duel, which Affleck wrote with good friend Matt Damon. Tap the bio link for more. | 📷: Jacopo Raule/Getty Images

node.text: This week's issue of PEOPLE explores eight unsolved cases of missing moms. “How can somebody disappear like smoke in the wind?” Prisma Reyes' stepfather asks in this week's issue. Pick up the issue on stands Friday, and tap the bio link for their stories.
